{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "hp-user-a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "HighPerformance User APIs",
    "description": "User-facing API collection for High-Performance E-Commerce Backend (`routes/api.php`).\n\nHow to use:\n1) Set `active_env` to `local` or `live`.\n2) Update `local` / `live` URLs if needed.\n3) Run **Auth > Login** (demo user) to auto-save bearer token (`token` + `userToken`).\n4) All other requests use Sanctum Bearer auth from the collection.\n\nDemo credentials:\n- email: `demo@highperformance.test`\n- password: `password`\n\nParallel programming features:\n- **Order** routes use capacity control + circuit breaker middleware.\n- **POST /order** reserves stock with DB locks, then queues invoice & notification jobs.\n- Run queue workers after placing an order: `php artisan queue:work --queue=invoices,notifications`\n\nNotes:\n- Responses wrap payload in `data` (see `BaseAction::success`).\n- **POST /order** builds from current cart then clears cart lines.\n- **POST /cart** upserts a single product line (`product_id`, `quantity`; use `0` to remove).\n- Login/Register disable auth; everything else expects a user token.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "const activeEnv = pm.collectionVariables.get('active_env') || 'local';",
          "const local = pm.collectionVariables.get('local') || 'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api';",
          "const live = pm.collectionVariables.get('live') || 'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api';",
          "const selectedBaseUrl = activeEnv === 'live' ? live : local;",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('base_url', selectedBaseUrl);",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('baseUrl', selectedBaseUrl);",
          "",
          "const token = pm.collectionVariables.get('token') || pm.collectionVariables.get('userToken') || '';",
          "if (token) {",
          "  pm.collectionVariables.set('token', token);",
          "  pm.collectionVariables.set('userToken', token);",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "pm.test('Response time is less than 5s', function () {",
          "  pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(5000);",
          "});"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      { "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "active_env", "value": "local" },
    { "key": "local", "value": "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api" },
    { "key": "live", "value": "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api" },
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api" },
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://127.0.0.1:8000/api" },
    { "key": "token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "userToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "categoryId", "value": "1" },
    { "key": "productId", "value": "1" },
    { "key": "orderId", "value": "1" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Ahmed Ali\",\n  \"email\": \"ahmed@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"secret123\",\n  \"password_confirmation\": \"secret123\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/register",
            "description": "Creates user + empty cart. Returns bearer token."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "let data = {}; try { data = pm.response.json(); } catch (e) {}",
                  "const token = data?.data?.token;",
                  "if (token) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('token', token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('userToken', token);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 201', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (Demo User)",
          "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"demo@highperformance.test\",\n  \"password\": \"password\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
            "description": "Seeded demo user from `DemoUserSeeder`."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "let data = {}; try { data = pm.response.json(); } catch (e) {}",
                  "const token = data?.data?.token;",
                  "if (token) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('token', token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('userToken', token);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Login successful', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('Token saved', function () { pm.expect(pm.collectionVariables.get('token')).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty; });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/logout"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Logout successful', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Product",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Products",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/product",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["product"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "category_id", "value": "{{categoryId}}", "description": "Filter (equal)", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "is_active", "value": "1", "description": "Filter (equal)", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "search", "value": "", "description": "Search name/description", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "page", "value": "1", "disabled": true }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "let data = {}; try { data = pm.response.json(); } catch (e) {}",
                  "const first = data?.data?.[0];",
                  "if (first?.id) pm.collectionVariables.set('productId', String(first.id));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Show Product",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/product/{{productId}}"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Cart",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Show Cart",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/cart"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Cart (Add / Change Qty)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"product_id\": {{productId}},\n  \"quantity\": 2\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/cart",
            "description": "Upserts one line. Set `quantity` to 0 to remove the product from cart."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Cart (Remove Line)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"product_id\": {{productId}},\n  \"quantity\": 0\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/cart"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Order",
      "description": "Protected by `capacity.control` and `circuit.breaker:orders` middleware.\nAfter success, run queue workers for invoice/notification jobs.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Orders",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/order",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["order"],
              "query": [{ "key": "page", "value": "1", "disabled": true }]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Show Order",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/order/{{orderId}}",
            "description": "Includes `invoice` and `notifications` when loaded."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Order (from cart)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"user_notes\": \"Leave at door\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/order",
            "description": "Uses current cart. Reserves stock with pessimistic locks (`InventoryService`). Dispatches `GenerateOrderInvoiceJob` and `SendOrderNotificationJob`. Cart is cleared after success."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "let data = {}; try { data = pm.response.json(); } catch (e) {}",
                  "const orderId = data?.data?.id;",
                  "if (orderId) pm.collectionVariables.set('orderId', String(orderId));",
                  "pm.test('Order created', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Parallel Demo",
      "description": "Helpers to demonstrate course requirements during presentation.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Order (stress — run in Collection Runner)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"user_notes\": \"concurrent test\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/order",
            "description": "Run with Collection Runner (iterations 10+) after adding items to cart. Watch for 503 CAPACITY_EXCEEDED when exceeding MAX_CONCURRENT_CHECKOUTS."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
